<!-- 03 INTRO -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="intro-grid">
      <div class="intro-body">
        <p class="section-number">01 — About This Service</p>
        <h2 class="section-title">A freezer failure in LA has a short window before food is at risk.</h2>

        <p>When a freezer stops holding temperature, the urgency is different from most appliance failures. A broken dishwasher is inconvenient. A freezer that climbs above 0°F puts hundreds of dollars of food at risk within hours — and in LA's warm ambient temperatures, it happens faster than in most cities. We treat freezer calls with that urgency.</p>

        <p>The failures are predictable. The defrost system is the most common culprit — when the defrost heater, defrost timer, or defrost thermostat fails, frost accumulates on the evaporator coils until airflow is completely blocked. The freezer runs continuously but can't circulate cold air. A weakening compressor or a slow refrigerant leak in the sealed system are the higher-severity failures that require more involved diagnosis. A worn door seal quietly lets warm air in 24 hours a day, forcing the compressor to compensate.</p>

        <p>Our technicians carry defrost components, evaporator fan motors, and thermostat assemblies for the brands they see most in LA. For the majority of freezer calls, the repair is completed same visit.</p>

        <div class="tip-box">
          <div class="tip-label">❄️ While You Wait for Us</div>
          <p>If your freezer is running but struggling to hold temperature, keep the door closed as much as possible — every opening lets in warm air and costs 20–30 minutes of recovery time. A full freezer holds temperature longer than an empty one. If it's completely off, most food stays safe for 24–48 hours with the door closed. Anything with ice crystals still present is generally safe to refreeze once repaired.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

