<section class="section section-black">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">02 — Freezer Types We Service</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Every configuration found in LA homes</h2>
    <p class="lead">From a basic chest freezer in a Burbank garage to a Sub-Zero column in a Beverly Hills kitchen — the failure modes differ by type and we come prepared for each.</p>

    <div class="type-grid">
      <div class="type-card">
        <div class="type-icon">📦</div>
        <h3>Chest Freezers</h3>
        <p>Common in garages and utility spaces. Large capacity, efficient design. Most failures: defrost system, thermostat, compressor, or start relay. In LA garages, heat-related compressor stress is the most frequent issue.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="type-card">
        <div class="type-icon">🗄️</div>
        <h3>Upright Freezers</h3>
        <p>More convenient access, more moving parts. Defrost system failures, evaporator fan motors, door gaskets, and temperature sensors are the common repairs. More susceptible to frost buildup than chest models.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="type-card">
        <div class="type-icon">🏠</div>
        <h3>Bottom-Freezer Refrigerators</h3>
        <p>The freezer drawer on a bottom-freezer fridge has its own defrost system and evaporator coils. When the freezer section fails while the fridge section works normally, it's almost always the defrost system or evaporator fan for that zone.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="type-card">
        <div class="type-icon">🧊</div>
        <h3>Built-In &amp; Column Freezers</h3>
        <p>Sub-Zero, Thermador, and Miele column freezers — common in Beverly Hills, Bel Air, and Hancock Park kitchens. Panel-ready access, OEM parts required, higher repair complexity. We carry parts for these specifically.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="type-card">
        <div class="type-icon">❄️</div>
        <h3>French Door Freezer Drawers</h3>
        <p>The bottom freezer on Samsung, LG, and KitchenAid French Door units has its own sealed system and defrost components. Ice maker issues in the freezer section are also common on these models.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="type-card">
        <div class="type-icon">🏢</div>
        <h3>Commercial Freezers</h3>
        <p>Reach-in and under-counter commercial units for restaurants and food businesses. Our commercial diagnostic fee is $120. We work on True, Turbo Air, Beverage-Air, and other commercial brands commonly found in LA kitchens.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
